subSubSection.paragraph:
Female. Length 8.2–9.5 mm . Similar to male. Apex of last ventrite truncate. Sternite VIII medially weakly sclerotized (
Fig. 18
), apex truncate with dense long setae, spiculum short; however, well sclerotized in individuals from high mountains (
Fig. 19
) with spiculum apically widened, separated from apex, apex subdivided into two at middle. Spermathecal receptaculum strongly swollen (
Fig. 26
), abruptly narrowed between receptaculum and pump, pump narrow and curved, spermathecal duct wide, slightly projecting into receptaculum. Gonocoxae (
Fig. 33
) separated, tubular, apex truncate, with four or five long setae.

